description: Alias tokens translate raw brand colors into semantic meaning. Alias is the only layer allowed to assign intent and group meaning. Alias tokens MUST always reference brand tokens.

globs: src/components/**/*.tsx

alwaysApply: true
---

## Color Rules

Primary = Purple
Information = Blue
Success = Green
Error = Red
Warning = Orange
Neutral = Grey
Foundations = Black & White
Not all scales must be aliased. 
Optional scales = secondary & tertiary
If brand scales exceed needs
Pause
Ask which scales should be aliased
Do not assume

---

## Scale Structure

Scales use a 100-1200 scale. Lower number is lighter and higher numbers are darker. 
Allowed Increments:
100 by default
50 when intermediate values are needed.
25 when further refinement is also needed.

---

## Other Instructions

Alias modes exist only when other brands are present.
Single brand design systems do not use multiple modes.
Additional modes require confirmation.
Font weights and styles can be pulled into the alias collection if multiple brands are required. 